name: inoutpainting_transparencies
author: YMGenesis
description: Example of using a mask to in/outpaint to fill transparencies in an image with an inpaint model. Drop/pass the image on/into the Image Primitive node on the left. First pass fills in the transparencies, second pass smooths/blends the edges of the subject.
notes:
V1.2 - changed colour correct references from source image with transparency to pathmatch filled & output of first pass. Final won't be so dark this way.

V1.1 - added patchmatch infilling of transparencies before sending to denoise latents (can produce better results instead of dark/black backgrounds).
